title: For Sale:  8mm Czech Mauser vz.24 tactical sportirized
postcontent:
Originally when I bought this rifle it was chambered in 7mm.  I re-chambered it in 8mm so it could shoot cheaper mil surplus rounds in that caliber and it would be easier to find factory rounds for hunting.  I put a new Yugo 8mm Mauser barrel on it and an ATI tactical stock.  AIM Sports scout scope mounted.  It does have a bent bolt so you can put a normal rifle scope on it but I like the performance and fast target acquisition a scout scope provides so I went that route.  

This rifle is extremely sound, rugged, well built, and in mint condition.  the Czechs made their Mausers almost better than the Germans.  They don't make rifles like they used to, there's not one ounce of recycled steel on this gun.  The barrel has only about 70 rounds through it and I've always cleaned it after shooting. The lands and grooves aka rifling are in mint condition.  The barrel is unfinished for looks, I always keep a light coating of rem-oil on it.  8mm is a nice round, similar to 30-06, .270, .303 etc.  

 I have 50 mil surplus rounds and 34 Remington Core-Lokt rounds, for hunting, to go with it.  

Would possibly consider a trade or partial trade.   If you have any questions let me know.  Buyer pays for background check.  Thanks.

title: For Sale/Trade:  PRICE DROP:::::::FN Hi-Power DA
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is my FN Hi-Power DA in VERY good condition. This is an all Belgium made firearm with all matching serial numbers. Not many of these were made and even less made their way into the USA. This model of the Hi-Power was designated for law enforcement usage only, which further contributed to its scarcity.

Further information on the gun: It was made from 83-87 and production ceased. It was made as the "BDA" in the USA and in Europe as the "DA" as is pictured here. Not very many of the "DA" models, like I have, made it to the USA. Thus, the rarity. The DA models that were made in Europe were designated for Law Enforcement usage and were rare in Europe as a result. 

Gun comes with FN carry case and the original magazine. Also comes with original cleaning kit provided by FN.
